    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Neologism used to refer to the "the binding of the years" that occured in Nahua culture at the end of a 52-year cycle in the solar calendar or xiuhpohualli. The ceremony in which the years were "tied" is known as New Fire.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000320/GRI-FloCo</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109721/GRI, FloCo terminology (2019-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>El neologismo se utiliza para referirse a la "atadura de los años" que ocurría en la cultura nahua al final de un ciclo de 52 años en el calendario solar o xiuhpohualli. La ceremonia en la que se "ataban" los años se conoce como Fuego Nuevo.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000320/GRI-FloCo</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109721/GRI, FloCo terminology (2019-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tlahtolchihchihualli motequihuia para momanextiz "xihuiilpilli" tlen panoyaya ipan macehualtlallamiccayotl nahuatl, itlamiyan ce ciclo tlen ompohualli huan mahtlactli huan ome xihuitl ipan tonalpohualli zo xiuhpohualli. Campeca tlen campa "moilpiyaya" xihuitl quiixmati quence Tlitl Yancuic.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Eastern Huasteca Nahuatl</Note_Language>
